./.title: DocumentBuilder Docs
./.body:
DocumentBuilder Docs
Naive's API

This API is  constructed by  extracting  the  more commonly
used and  common  functions  when I developing  games. It 
may  not be very  suitable  for  large-scale projects and it is 
not a  deep study of a  certain  functional area, but I believe 
it is  good  for  small  and  medium-sized  projects. Such  as
GameJem etc.
This Document Book contains all document about my API's 
class and function. Hope it can help you to  understand  my
tools easily. If you have any question, there is  my  Contact 
Information.

GettingStarted.html.title: Intro
GettingStarted.html.body:
GettingStarted
Intro
Here will show you how to create your own document.
All steps can be finish in this window. For customized, 
you can do it in UnityEditor or even in Scripts.

GettingStarted/1_CreateBookRoot.html.title: 1_CreateBookRoot
GettingStarted/1_CreateBookRoot.html.body:
1_CreateBookRoot
1.1 Create Your Book Root
You can skip this step if you want to put your document below mine.
Create SODocInformation as BookRoot
( Assets / Create / Naive API / Document Information )


1.2 Add it to the DocBookList
( Edit / Project Settings / DocumentBuilder Settings)


1.3 Now you can found it in Book selection menu

GettingStarted/2_CreateSubPage.html.title: 2_CreateSubPage
GettingStarted/2_CreateSubPage.html.body:
2_CreateSubPage
2.1 Select your Book and change into Edit Mode


2.2 Edit Mode will show you all elements can edit.
it's same with ScriptableObject's Inspector. So you can also 
edit it on Inspector,  but in this  window is more  convenient.




Editing Target
The ScriptableObject asset that you are editing.




Name
Little title display at UpLeft


Document Icon Type
Little icon display in left Menu


Sub Pages
Will show it's subpage in left Menu




2.3 Click AddSubpage button

Now you can select exist document or use Auto Create

Exist document
 Create DocInformation in same way as create BookRoot
 and select or drag it into field.

AutoCreate
 Click AutoCreate and name the new page. If the name is
 not allow,  you will  not be  able to  click "Create" button.
 It will auto create SubFolder in editing target's folder and
 generate asset in it.



Now it will appear in menu

GettingStarted/3_EditInformation.html.title: 3_EditInformation
GettingStarted/3_EditInformation.html.body:
3_EditInformation
Description
DocInformation is construct by many DocComponent.
You can add  as  many as  you  want.
You can checkout DocComponent type's detail in the next part.

Add New DocComponent
Just use Add or Paste, 
but notice that you can't Paste before Copy


Basic Edit Function




▲ & ▼
Change the sort order of components




Copy
Copy this component into System Clipboard


Paste
Paste component from System Clipboard


Dup
Duplicate this component


Type
Select this component's type




DocComponent Template
After creating some general component structures, 
you can store  them  as  Templates,  which can be 
called directly in the future.




Save as new
Save this component structures




Loas from old
Load structures saved before


edit
You can delete useless Template here

Advanced.html.title: intro
Advanced.html.body:
Advanced
Here will show you some advanced use example.
Overview:

Open Docs window with specific book root
Export docs with markdown format

Advanced/Add Docs Menuitem.html.title: Add Docs Menuitem
Advanced/Add Docs Menuitem.html.body:
Add Docs Menuitem
You can add your menuitem by open specific book root
Just make a function like below, notice that menuitem 
only run in Editor, so don't do it at runtime script.

You can also use DocumentBuilder to write your package's 
offline docs, just remember to add Asset Store dependencies.

Advanced/Export as Markdown.html.title: Export as Markdown
Advanced/Export as Markdown.html.body:
Export as Markdown
To export a book into markdown format :
goto " Edit / Project Settings / DocumentBuilder Settings "
and see " Esport " section like below


Path is export root folder
root is the book root, notice that all of its subPages      will export at the same time
After generated, it will also generate  a  SUMMARY.md  file
it contains docs struct and releated-path link, you can use
it to export static site with using other html tool like GitBook.
